        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Mail::setBodyText() currently only allows a specific type of MIME part to be set.  Users should be able to define parameters for the MIME part.  For example, users should be able to set the encoding to 7bit, instead of the default QUOTEDPRINTABLE.\n\nPerhaps setBodyText() should optionally accept an instance of Zend_Mime_Part?"
        },
